              Claude Commander (cc) -- Keyboard Help

  NAVIGATION
    Up/Down ......... move cursor          Tab ........... switch panel
    PgUp/PgDn ....... page                 Home/End ...... top / bottom
    Enter ........... open dir / run       Backspace ..... parent dir
    Insert .......... tag / untag entry

  FUNCTION KEYS
    F1 .. this help          F3 .. view          F4 .. edit (CCEDIT)
    F5 .. copy               F6 .. move/rename    F7 .. make dir
    F8 .. delete             F9 .. menu           F10 . quit
    Alt-F1/F2 ....... change drive (left / right panel)
    Alt-F7 .......... find files by name (CCFIND)
    Alt-F8 .......... search file contents / grep (CCGREP)

  DISPLAY / SELECT
    Ctrl-F1..F4 ..... sort by name / ext / size / date
    Ctrl-F5 ......... cycle column: size / date / time / attributes
    Ctrl-F6 ......... incremental quick-search
    Ctrl-F7/F8 ...... tag / untag files by *.mask
    Ctrl-A .......... edit file attributes (Read-only/Hidden/System/Archive)
    Ctrl-F9 ......... list archive contents (CCZIP)

  DISPLAY (cont.)
    Long names ...... the cursor file's long name shows on the command row
                      when an LFN provider is active (Win9x DOS / DOSLFN);
                      on plain DOS the 8.3 name is used.

  EXTERNAL TOOLS (type the name at the prompt, then Enter)
    CCHEX <file> .... hex + ASCII dump of any file (binary viewer)
    CCGREP w d m .... search file contents (also Alt-F8)
    CCFIND p d ...... find files by name (also Alt-F7)
    CCZIP <zip> ..... list a ZIP archive (also Ctrl-F9)

  CONFIG
    cc.ini .......... set initial "sort" and "columns" options
    cc.lng .......... translate the F-key bar (copy da.lng to cc.lng)

  Scroll this help with Up/Down/PgUp/PgDn; press Esc, q, F1 or F10 to close.
